<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3F6A80F7E9957F1850BEA1" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3F6A80F7E9957F1850BEA1" blockId="196.[2068,2663,723,1151]" lastBlockId="196.[1453,2663,1157,3323]" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80F751957F1704B871" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[2221,2308,806,835]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80F6E5957F1789B871" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[2329,2441,806,835]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">muricola</taxonomicName>
species group. Closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80F6CF9510179DB858" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[2355,2461,841,874]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">M. ater</taxonomicName>
(which see). Based on genetic data, morphometric data, and dentition, three taxa (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80F5EB95F8164AB8D3" authorityName="Kishida" authorityYear="1932" baseAuthorityName="Kishida" baseAuthorityYear="1932" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Submyotodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="latirostris">latirostris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80F798959116F4B8D3" authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1859" box="[2148,2292,968,993]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caliginosus">caliginosus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80F6AA959117F7B8D3" authorityName="MilneEdwards" authorityYear="1872" box="[2390,2551,968,993]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="moupinensis">moupinensis</taxonomicName>
) previously considered races of this species have been moved to genus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80F64F9256145FBF02" authorityName="Ziegler" authorityYear="2003" box="[2483,2655,1039,1072]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Submyotodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Submyotodon</taxonomicName>
, hitherto known only from fossil material. Populations of 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF3F6A80F7049207179ABF4D" box="[2296,2458,1118,1151]" name="Philippines" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">Philippines</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF3F6A80F61192071463BF4D" box="[2541,2659,1118,1151]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
previously attributed to this species are now placed tentatively in M. brown: (which see). Internal taxonomy requires revision: populations of 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF3F6A80F70E92F51777BFFF" box="[2290,2423,1196,1229]" name="Indonesia" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">Moluccas</collectingCountry>
and Lesser Sundas represent a species complex, as none of the individual island populations seem to cluster together monophyletically. Bornean populations form a monophyletic clade that is sister to a clade formed by South-east Asian and Sumatran populations. Form niasensis (Nias, off western 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF3F6A80F80C93131669BE59" box="[2032,2153,1354,1387]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
) may be a distinct race or species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
